  "texts": [
    "This further supports the use of physically interpretable features, such as those used in this article, which hopefully provides some structure to the feature space, that leads to a sensible M-JDA mapping.",
    "In universal domain adaptation scenarios four to six (where there are fewer classes in the source domain than the target), it is not possible to obtain the F 1 scores for a target class if it does not appear in the source domain.",
    "Here, the target pseudo-labels are only assigned from existing classes in the source domain, which may not always correspond to the same damage scenario, as seen in Figure 10b.",
    "As a result, the classification performances decrease in Table 7, as expected.",
    "In order to investigate the influence of the initial target pseudo-labels from the metrics-informed approach on the JDA method when considering a class imbalance, Figures 11 and 12 are presented."
